extends layout

append head
  link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.5.0/themes/prism.min.css")

block content
  .section.wrapper
    h2(class="ui centered header") And your token is...

  .section.wrapper
    .ui.form
      .ui.field
        textarea(readonly rows="3")= token
        small *Don't lose this token, and remember to bookmark this page in case you need to come back.

  .section.wrapper
    h2 Setup

  .section.wrapper
    p
      a(
        target="_blank"
        href="https://github.com/axios/axios"
      ) Axios 
      | is a required dependency. You can include the CDN for it with this script:

  .section.wrapper
    pre
      code(class="language-js") &lt;script src=&quot;https://unpkg.com/axios/dist/axios.min.js&quot;&gt;

  .section.wrapper
    p After axios, include the Prefixy script:

  .section.wrapper
    pre
      code(class="language-js") &lt;script src=&quot;https://prefixy.io/prefixy.js&quot;&gt;

  .section.wrapper
    p Then create a new instance of Prefixy with your input field and token. For example:

  .section.wrapper
    pre
      code(class="language-js")
        | &lt;script&gt;
        |   var myInput = document.getElementById(‘my-input’);
        | 
        |   new Prefixy({
        |     input: myInput,
        |     token: #{token}
        |   });
        | &lt;/script&gt;

  .section.wrapper
    p If your input is part of a form, make sure that the form element is also included in the options:

  .section.wrapper
    pre
      code(class="language-js")
        | &lt;script&gt;
        |   var myInput = document.getElementById(‘my-input’);
        |   var myForm = document.getElementById(‘my-form’);
        |
        |   new Prefixy({
        |     input: myInput,
        |     form: myForm,
        |     token: #{token}
        |   });
        | &lt;/script&gt;

  .section.wrapper
    h2 Additional options

  .section.wrapper
    dl
      dt: em suggestionCount
      dd The maximum number of suggestions that should be displayed at any one time to the user as they type. Defaults to 5 if not specified.
      dt: em minChars
      dd The minimum number of characters a user must enter before suggestions are displayed. Defaults to 1 if not specified.
      dt: em delay
      dd The amount of time, in milliseconds, to wait after a character has been typed, before sending a request for suggestions. Defaults to 0 if not specified.

  .section.wrapper
    h3 Full Example
    p Here’s an example of including the scripts in your html with all of the options specified:

  .section.wrapper
    pre
      code(class="language-js")
        | &lt;html&gt;
        |   &lt;body&gt;
        |
        |     ...
        |
        |     &lt;script src=&quot;https://unpkg.com/axios/dist/axios.min.js&quot;&gt;
        |     &lt;script src=&quot;https://prefixy.io/prefixy.js&quot;&gt;
        |     &lt;script&gt;
        |       var myInput = document.getElementById(‘my-input’);
        |       var myForm = document.getElementById(‘my-form’);
        |    
        |       new Prefixy({
        |         input: myInput,
        |         form: myForm,
        |         token: #{token},
        |         suggestionCount: 5,
        |         minChars: 1,
        |         delay: 50
        |       });
        |     &lt;/script&gt;
        |   &lt;/body&gt;
        | &lt;/html&gt;

  .section.wrapper
    h2 You're all set!
    p If you need more help, see our
      a(
        target="_blank"
        href="https://github.com/jayshenk/prefixy/tree/master/docs"
      )  documentation on github here.

append body
  script(src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.5.0/prism.min.js")
